    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1038_s41467_020_18035_1__task_001/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The TOBIAS bias correction module (named ATACorrect) utilizes a dinucleotide weight matrix (DWM) to estimate the background bias of the Tn5 transposase (Fig. 1c). This DWM is used to calculate an expected Tn5 signal for each genomic region, representing the influence of the Tn5 bias (Fig. 1c; expected cutsites). Subtracting these expected cuts from the uncorrected signals yields a corrected track, highlighting the effect of protein binding",
      "asbval:note": "The research question is directly answered in the paper. ATACorrect uses a dinucleotide weight matrix to estimate Tn5 bias, calculates expected Tn5 cutsites, and subtracts them from observed signals to produce bias-corrected tracks.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-020-18035-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "How does the TOBIAS ATACorrect module correct for Tn5 transposase insertion bias in ATAC-seq data to produce bias-corrected signal tracks?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:16:06.174403+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1038_s41467_020_18035_1__task_001/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Here we present TOBIAS, a comprehensive, accurate, and fast footprinting framework enabling genome-wide investigation of TF binding dynamics for hundreds of TFs simultaneously.",
      "asbval:note": "TOBIAS is the primary tool presented in the paper and is used throughout for ATAC-seq footprinting analysis including bias correction.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-020-18035-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "TOBIAS",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:16:06.174403+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1038_s41467_020_18035_1__task_001/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Subtracting these expected cuts from the uncorrected signals yields a corrected track, highlighting the effect of protein binding (details are available in Supplementary Methods part 1).",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes producing 'corrected tracks' from the ATACorrect module, but does not explicitly specify the file format as 'bigWig'. The paper mentions UCSC track hubs and visualization in IGV, which are compatible with bigWig, but the specific format is not stated in the main text. The output is a corrected signal track, but the format specification is not explicitly confirmed.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-020-18035-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Bias-corrected bigWig signal track",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:16:06.174403+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1038_s41467_020_18035_1__task_001/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The card focuses narrowly on the ATACorrect bias-correction step, which is one component of the broader TOBIAS framework. The paper presents TOBIAS as a comprehensive footprinting framework with multiple modules (bias correction, footprinting, differential binding, visualization, network inference). The card's scope is appropriately aligned with the paper's treatment of this specific module.",
        "The paper demonstrates ATACorrect's performance in the context of full ATAC-seq footprinting analysis, including validation against ChIP-seq data and application to developmental biology. The card's research question is narrowly focused on the technical mechanism of bias correction, which is well-supported but represents only one aspect of the paper's contributions."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 2,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:16:06.174403+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1038_s41467_020_18035_1__task_002/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The corrected cutsites enable calculation of footprint scores with a scoring function taking into account both the accessibility and depth of the local footprint",
      "asbval:note": "Passage 5 explicitly describes the footprint scoring step applied to corrected cutsites. Passage 6 further elaborates that the TOBIAS score combines depletion and accessibility, contrasting with prior methods like FOS that use only depletion.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-020-18035-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "How does TOBIAS compute footprint scores from bias-corrected ATAC-seq signal data across accessible chromatin regions?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:16:17.396369+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
