    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1038_s41467_020_18035_1__task_004/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The card describes a relatively straightforward footprinting analysis task, while the paper presents TOBIAS as a comprehensive framework with multiple advanced features including bias correction (ATACorrect), differential binding analysis, TF network inference, and motif clustering. The card captures only the core footprinting visualization aspect.",
        "The paper applies TOBIAS to specific biological questions (zygotic genome activation, Dux regulation) with complex multi-condition comparisons, whereas the card frames it as a general analytical task on a public dataset without specifying biological context."
      ],
