      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The skepticism towards DGF has been driven by the discovery that enzymes used in chromatin accessibility assays (e.g., DNase-I) are biased towards certain sequence compositions... The influence of Tn5 transposase bias in the context of ATAC-seq footprinting has, however, only been described very recently and still represents an uncertainty during discovery of true footprints.",
