    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/bam-to-bigwig-conversion/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "TOBIAS is a collection of command-line tools utilizing a minimal input of ATAC-seq reads, TF motifs and genome information (Fig. 1b) to perform all levels of footprinting analysis including bias correction (Fig. 1c), footprinting (Fig. 1d), and comparison between conditions (Fig. 1e). Furthermore, TOBIAS includes a variety of auxiliary tools such as TF network inference and visualization of footprints",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes TOBIAS producing bias-corrected signal tracks and visualization, but does not explicitly describe a BAM-to-BigWig conversion step. The paper mentions TOBIAS outputs corrected cutsites and footprint scores, and includes visualization modules, but the specific BAM-to-BigWig conversion workflow is not detailed in the passages. The paper does reference UCSC track hubs and visualization in genome browsers, suggesting BigWig outputs exist, but the conversion process itself is not explicitly documented in the provided passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-020-18035-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "bam-to-bigwig-conversion",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Convert bias-corrected ATAC-seq signal data from BAM format to BigWig format for visualization and downstream footprinting analysis.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:19:59.985313+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/bam-to-bigwig-conversion/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The TOBIAS bias correction module (named ATACorrect) utilizes a dinucleotide weight matrix (DWM) to estimate the background bias of the Tn5 transposase (Fig. 1c). This DWM is used to calculate an expected Tn5 signal for each genomic region, representing the influence of the Tn5 bias (Fig. 1c; expected cutsites). Subtracting these expected cuts from the uncorrected signals yields a corrected track, highlighting the effect of protein binding",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms ATACorrect produces corrected signal tracks and mentions visualization, but does not explicitly name 'ScoreBigwig' as a downstream tool in the provided passages. The paper does describe footprint scoring calculation but the specific tool name 'ScoreBigwig' is not mentioned in the passages provided.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-020-18035-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "bam-to-bigwig-conversion",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "After running TOBIAS ATACorrect to generate bias-corrected signal tracks from aligned ATAC-seq reads. Use this skill when you have corrected cutsite signal (as .bw or equivalent intermediate format) that must be visualized across the genome or fed into footprint scoring tools lik",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:19:59.985313+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/bam-to-bigwig-conversion/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The TOBIAS bias correction module (named ATACorrect) utilizes a dinucleotide weight matrix (DWM) to estimate the background bias of the Tn5 transposase (Fig. 1c). This DWM is used to calculate an expected Tn5 signal for each genomic region, representing the influence of the Tn5 bias (Fig. 1c; expected cutsites). Subtracting these expected cuts from the uncorrected signals yields a corrected track, highlighting the effect of protein binding",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms ATACorrect produces corrected signal tracks, but does not explicitly state the output format as '_corrected.bw' or confirm BigWig as the primary output format in the provided passages. The paper references visualization in UCSC genome browser and track hubs, which implies BigWig format, but the explicit file naming convention and format are not stated in the passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-020-18035-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "bam-to-bigwig-conversion",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "TOBIAS ATACorrect produces bias-corrected signal as primary bigWig output; generates _corrected.bw file from aligned BAM and reference genome",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:19:59.985313+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
