    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/chromatin-accessibility-binding-status-classification/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "TOBIAS can unveil complex TF dynamics during zygotic genome activation... TOBIAS can promote biological insight by predicting entire TF-activation networks... TOBIAS can indicate the kinetics between TF expression (mRNA) and the actual binding activity of their translated proteins.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper demonstrates use of TOBIAS for differential binding analysis, network inference, and kinetic studies as described in the scope.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-020-18035-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "chromatin-accessibility-binding-status-classification",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Use this skill when chromatin accessibility alone is insufficient\u2014you require binding status labels for downstream differential binding analysis, network inference, or kinetic studies.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:20:34.940646+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/chromatin-accessibility-binding-status-classification/008",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Recent advances have enabled the application of ATAC-seq in single cells, but this generates sparse matrices, rendering footprinting approaches on single cells elusive. However, we speculate that by creating aggregated pseudo-bulk signals from large clustered single-cell ATAC datasets, DGF analysis might also become possible in single cells.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly acknowledges that single-cell ATAC-seq without aggregation is problematic for footprinting due to sparsity.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-020-18035-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "chromatin-accessibility-binding-status-classification",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Input is single-cell ATAC-seq without pseudobulk aggregation\u2014individual cell resolution lacks sufficient read depth for reliable footprint detection",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:20:34.940646+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/chromatin-accessibility-binding-status-classification/009",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Strikingly, we observed that these defined footprints were not detectable without TOBIAS-mediated Tn5 bias correction... This demonstrates that failure to correct for Tn5 bias can lead to false negative footprints, while bias correction uncovers the true amount of measurable footprints to be above 50%.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper demonstrates that Tn5 bias correction is essential to avoid false negatives and obscured footprints.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-020-18035-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "chromatin-accessibility-binding-status-classification",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Tn5 insertion bias has not been corrected\u2014biased cutsites can mimic or obscure true footprints; apply ATACorrect before classification",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:20:34.940646+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/chromatin-accessibility-footprint-visualization/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "TOBIAS includes a variety of auxiliary tools such as TF network inference and visualization of footprints, which allow for various downstream analysis. The corrected cutsites enable calculation of footprint scores with a scoring function taking into account both the accessibility and depth of the local footprint. This continuous footprint score is correlated with the presence of transcription factor binding sites in the genome.",
      "asbval:note": "The research question is directly supported by the paper's description of TOBIAS visualization capabilities for footprints and comparative analysis across conditions.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-020-18035-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "chromatin-accessibility-footprint-visualization",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Visualize transcription factor footprints in ATAC-seq data by aggregating corrected Tn5 insertion signals around known transcription factor binding sites, enabling direct inspection of protein-induced depletion patterns and comparative analysis across conditions.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:20:53.068753+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/chromatin-accessibility-footprint-visualization/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The TOBIAS bias correction module (named ATACorrect) utilizes a dinucleotide weight matrix (DWM) to estimate the background bias of the Tn5 transposase. TOBIAS then calculates the expected Tn5 cutsites per region, which represent the background probability of Tn5 insertion.",
      "asbval:note": "ATACorrect is explicitly named and described as the bias correction module within TOBIAS.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-020-18035-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "chromatin-accessibility-footprint-visualization",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "TOBIAS ATACorrect",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:20:53.068753+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/chromatin-accessibility-footprint-visualization/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "After the main TOBIAS analysis, a variety of downstream analysis can be applied including visualization of local and aggregated footprints across conditions. For selected TFs with known roles in early development originating from four clusters, an aggregated footprinting plot matrix for all associated transcription factor binding sites is shown.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes aggregated footprint visualization as a core TOBIAS feature, though the specific module name 'PlotAggregate' is not explicitly mentioned in passages; however, the functionality is clearly present.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-020-18035-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "chromatin-accessibility-footprint-visualization",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "TOBIAS PlotAggregate",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:20:53.068753+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/chromatin-accessibility-footprint-visualization/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "TF activity scores from TOBIAS are Z-score transformed across rows. Blue color indicates low activity, red color indicates high activity. In order to visualize cluster trends, each cluster is associated with a mean trend line (left to right) and timepoint specific boxplots respectively.",
      "asbval:note": "Heatmap visualization is demonstrated in the paper, though the specific module name 'PlotHeatmap' is not explicitly stated in the passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-020-18035-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "chromatin-accessibility-footprint-visualization",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "TOBIAS PlotHeatmap",
