    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/chromatin-accessibility-footprint-visualization/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Here we present TOBIAS, a comprehensive, accurate, and fast footprinting framework enabling genome-wide investigation of TF binding dynamics for hundreds of TFs simultaneously. TOBIAS is a collection of command-line tools utilizing a minimal input of ATAC-seq reads, TF motifs and genome information to perform all levels of footprinting analysis including bias correction, footprinting, and comparison between conditions.",
      "asbval:note": "TOBIAS is the primary tool described throughout the paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-020-18035-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "chromatin-accessibility-footprint-visualization",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "TOBIAS (general tool)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:20:53.068753+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/chromatin-accessibility-footprint-visualization/008",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To confirm that TOBIAS-based footprinting scores are indeed associated with leaving bona fide footprints, we utilized the ability to visualize aggregated footprint plots as implemented within the framework. Indeed, bias corrected footprint scores were highly congruent with explicitly defined footprints.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper demonstrates validation of footprinting quality through visualization and comparison across conditions.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-020-18035-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "chromatin-accessibility-footprint-visualization",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Use this skill after performing Tn5 bias correction and footprint scoring on ATAC-seq BAM files when you need to inspect the spatial distribution of Tn5 insertions around transcription factor binding sites, validate footprinting quality, or communicate differential TF occupancy p",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:20:53.068753+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/chromatin-accessibility-footprint-visualization/009",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Strikingly, we observed that these defined footprints were not detectable without TOBIAS-mediated Tn5 bias correction. The skepticism towards DGF has been driven by the discovery that enzymes used in chromatin accessibility assays are biased towards certain sequence compositions.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly demonstrates that uncorrected signals fail to reveal footprints due to Tn5 bias.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-020-18035-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "chromatin-accessibility-footprint-visualization",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Input BAM files have not undergone Tn5 bias correction; uncorrected insertion signals contain substantial sequence bias artifacts that will obscure true footprints.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:20:53.068753+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/chromatin-accessibility-footprint-visualization/010",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Among these is the need of high-quality TF motifs for matching footprint scores to individual TFs with high confidence. In other words, while the binding of a TF might create an effect that can be interpreted as a footprint, without a known motif, this effect cannot be matched to the corresponding TF.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper identifies TF motifs as a critical requirement for meaningful footprint analysis.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-020-18035-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "chromatin-accessibility-footprint-visualization",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "You lack annotated transcription factor binding site coordinates or motif predictions; visualization aggregates only meaningful signal when centered on true/predicted TFBS.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:20:53.068753+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/chromatin-accessibility-occupancy-prediction/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "TOBIAS is a collection of command-line tools utilizing a minimal input of ATAC-seq reads, TF motifs and genome information (Fig. 1b) to perform all levels of footprinting analysis including bias correction (Fig. 1c), footprinting (Fig. 1d), and comparison between conditions (Fig. 1e).",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes TOBIAS performing footprinting analysis with bias correction and comparison between conditions. The research question accurately reflects the core functionality described.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-020-18035-1",
