    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/tf-binding-site-classification/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The TOBIAS bias correction module (named ATACorrect) utilizes a dinucleotide weight matrix (DWM) to estimate the background bias of the Tn5 transposase (Fig. 1c). This DWM is used to calculate an expected Tn5 signal for each genomic region, representing the influence of the Tn5 bias",
