      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/tf-binding-site-classification/009",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "While ATAC-seq can uncover accessible regions where TFs might bind, reliable identification of specific TF binding sites (TFBS) still relies on chromatin immunoprecipitation methods such as ChIP-seq. However, ChIP-seq methods require high input cell numbers, are limited to one TF per assay, and are further restricted to TFs for which antibodies are readily available.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper contrasts ATAC-seq footprinting with ChIP-seq as alternative methods, but does not discuss CUT&RUN. TOBIAS is designed for ATAC-seq, not ChIP-seq or CUT&RUN as primary input.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-020-18035-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "tf-binding-site-classification",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "You are analyzing ChIP-seq or CUT&RUN data instead",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:23:20.689742+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/tn5-insertion-bias-correction/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The influence of Tn5 transposase bias in the context of ATAC-seq footprinting has, however, only been described very recently and still represents an uncertainty during discovery of true footprints... The TOBIAS bias correction module (named ATACorrect) utilizes a dinucleotide weight matrix (DWM) to estimate the background bias of the Tn5 transposase... Subtracting these expected cuts from the uncorrected signals yields a corrected track, highlighting the effect of protein binding",
      "asbval:note": "Claim is fully supported. Paper explicitly describes Tn5 bias correction as essential for revealing true footprints and describes the ATACorrect module's function.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-020-18035-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "tn5-insertion-bias-correction",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Corrects systematic sequence preferences in Tn5 transposase insertion patterns within ATAC-seq data to reveal true transcription factor footprints. This bias correction is essential for accurate downstream footprinting analysis, as uncorrected insertion bias can obscure protein-b",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:23:43.096323+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/tn5-insertion-bias-correction/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The TOBIAS bias correction module (named ATACorrect) utilizes a dinucleotide weight matrix (DWM) to estimate the background bias of the Tn5 transposase",
