    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/tn5-insertion-bias-correction/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "the discovery that enzymes used in chromatin accessibility assays (e.g., DNase-I) are biased towards certain sequence compositions... The influence of Tn5 transposase bias in the context of ATAC-seq footprinting has, however, only been described very recently and still represents an uncertainty during discovery of true footprints",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms that Tn5 bias masks true footprints and that bias correction is needed to reveal them.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-020-18035-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "tn5-insertion-bias-correction",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "The skill is triggered when raw insertion signal contains confounding transposase sequence preferences that would mask the depletion patterns (footprints) characteristic of transcription factor binding.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:23:43.096323+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/tn5-insertion-position-extraction-and-counting/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "TOBIAS is a collection of command-line tools utilizing a minimal input of ATAC-seq reads, TF motifs and genome information (Fig. 1b) to perform all levels of footprinting analysis including bias correction (Fig. 1c), footprinting (Fig. 1d), and comparison between conditions (Fig. 1e)... The corrected cutsites enable calculation of footprint scores with a scoring function taking into account both the accessibility and depth of the local footprint... This continuous footprint score is correlated with the presence of transcription factor binding sites in the genome, and a threshold is set to distinguish between bound and unbound sites.",
      "asbval:note": "The research question accurately describes the core workflow: extracting Tn5 insertion positions from ATAC-seq BAM files, aggregating them across genomic windows, and using depletion patterns to detect TF footprints. This is explicitly demonstrated in the paper's methodology and figures.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-020-18035-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "tn5-insertion-position-extraction-and-counting",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Extract precise Tn5 transposase insertion coordinates from aligned ATAC-seq BAM files and aggregate insertion counts across fixed-width genomic windows to quantify local cleavage patterns. This skill enables detection of transcription factor footprints\u2014characteristic depletion si",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:23:55.038774+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/tn5-insertion-position-extraction-and-counting/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The TOBIAS bias correction module (named ATACorrect) utilizes a dinucleotide weight matrix (DWM) to estimate the background bias of the Tn5 transposase (Fig. 1c). This DWM is used to calculate an expected Tn5 signal for each genomic region, representing the influence of the Tn5 bias (Fig. 1c; expected cutsites). Subtracting these expected cuts from the uncorrected signals yields a corrected track, highlighting the effect of protein binding.",
      "asbval:note": "ATACorrect is explicitly named and described as the bias correction module within TOBIAS.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-020-18035-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "tn5-insertion-position-extraction-and-counting",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "TOBIAS ATACorrect - Bias-correction of Tn5 cutsite signal to remove sequence preferences of Tn5 transposase, improving accuracy of insertion position counts for downstream footprinting",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:23:55.038774+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/tn5-insertion-position-extraction-and-counting/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The corrected cutsites enable calculation of footprint scores with a scoring function taking into account both the accessibility and depth of the local footprint (as depicted in the box labeled 'Calculation of footprint scores'). This continuous footprint score is correlated with the presence of transcription factor binding sites in the genome, and a threshold is set to distinguish between bound and unbound sites.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes footprint score calculation as a core TOBIAS function, but does not explicitly name a module called 'ScoreBigwig'. The functionality is present (score calculation from corrected signals), but the specific tool name cannot be verified from the passages provided.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-020-18035-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "tn5-insertion-position-extraction-and-counting",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "TOBIAS ScoreBigwig - Calculate footprint scores from corrected Tn5 insertion signals across genomic windows to quantify footprint depth and distinguish bound sites",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:23:55.038774+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/tn5-insertion-position-extraction-and-counting/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "After the main TOBIAS analysis, a variety of downstream analysis can be applied including visualization of local and aggregated footprints across conditions, comparison of binding specificity between individual transcription factors and TF network prediction.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper confirms TOBIAS includes visualization of aggregated footprints, but does not explicitly name a module called 'PlotAggregate'. The functionality is present but the specific tool name is not verified.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-020-18035-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
