    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/transcription-factor-motif-matching/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "TOBIAS uses reads from ATAC-seq, transcription factor motifs and sequence annotation in standard formats as input... The corrected cutsites enable calculation of footprint scores... This continuous footprint score is correlated with the presence of transcription factor binding sites in the genome, and a threshold is set to distinguish between bound and unbound sites... If multiple conditions are investigated, the differential binding module summarizes individual site scores (upper black box) for each TF, and compares them between conditions.",
      "asbval:note": "Scope description aligns with paper's description of TOBIAS workflow and capabilities.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-020-18035-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "transcription-factor-motif-matching",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When to use: You have corrected ATAC-seq footprint scores (from ATACorrect and ScoreBigwig) at open chromatin regions and a motif database (e.g., JASPAR PWMs), and you need to determine which TF motif matches are actually occupied across one or more experimental conditions.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:25:03.425522+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/transcription-factor-motif-matching/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The first step of the TOBIAS footprinting pipeline is Tn5 bias correction... Subtracting these expected cuts from the uncorrected signals yields a corrected track, highlighting the effect of protein binding... Importantly, the FPD's of unbound sites are minimally affected by bias correction, indicating that bias correction only uncovers footprints for truly bound sites.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper emphasizes that bias correction is a prerequisite step in the pipeline.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-020-18035-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "transcription-factor-motif-matching",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When NOT to use: Input footprint scores are uncorrected or not derived from ATAC-seq Tn5 insertion patterns; use ATACorrect first.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:25:03.425522+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/transcription-factor-motif-matching/008",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The corrected cutsites enable calculation of footprint scores with a scoring function taking into account both the accessibility and depth of the local footprint... This continuous footprint score is correlated with the presence of transcription factor binding sites in the genome, and a threshold is set to distinguish between bound and unbound sites.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms that footprint scores must be calculated before binding site classification, but does not explicitly name 'ScoreBigwig' as the tool that performs this step.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-020-18035-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "transcription-factor-motif-matching",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When NOT to use: You only have raw ATAC-seq peaks without footprint score calculations; ScoreBigwig must precede BINDetect.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:25:03.425522+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/transcription-factor-motif-matching/009",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "TF motifs were downloaded from JASPAR CORE 2018, the JASPAR PBM HOMEO collection and Hocomoco V11 databases... Due to the redundancy of motifs between JASPAR and Hocomoco, we further filtered the TF motifs to one motif per gene, preferentially choosing motifs originating from mouse/human, respectively.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes motif processing and filtering but does not name 'FormatMotifs' as the tool. The functionality of motif standardization is implied but the specific tool name is not confirmed.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41467-020-18035-1",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "transcription-factor-motif-matching",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When NOT to use: Your motif database is not in JASPAR or TOBIAS-compatible PWM format; use FormatMotifs to convert first.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T19:25:03.425522+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
